<ns528:section xmlns:ns528="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.solms.training.courses.MDA.MDA">

  <ns529:title xmlns:ns529="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Model Driven Architecture (MDA)</ns529:title>
  <ns530:para xmlns:ns530="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    This course aims to provide a solid understanding of the rationale and benefits as well as the technical realization
    of OMG's Model Driven Architecture (MDA).
  </ns530:para>
  
  <ns531:section xmlns:ns531="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.solms.training.courses.MDA.targetAudience">
    <ns532:title xmlns:ns532="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">For whom is the course meant?</ns532:title>
    <ns533:para xmlns:ns533="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
       The course targets architects, designers and project managers who would like to understand the purpose, benefits
       as well as the practical realization of a model driven architecture.
    </ns533:para>
  </ns531:section>
  
  <ns534:section xmlns:ns534="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.solms.training.courses.MDA.prerequisites">
    <ns535:title xmlns:ns535="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Prerequisites</ns535:title>
    <ns536:para xmlns:ns536="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      Candidates should have prior experience in designing systems and should have some background in using
      the Unified Modeling Language (UML) for Modeling systems. Having attended the
     <ns537:link xmlns:ns537="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" linkend="resources.information.solms.training.courses.OOAD.OOAD">
       Object-Oriented Analysis and Design using UML</ns537:link> course and/or the 
      <ns538:link xmlns:ns538="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" linkend="resources.information.solms.training.courses.Architecture.Architecture">
        Architecture</ns538:link> course would provide a suitable background for this course.
   </ns536:para>
  </ns534:section>
  
  <ns539:section xmlns:ns539="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.solms.training.courses.MDA.outcomes">
    <ns540:title xmlns:ns540="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Outcomes</ns540:title>
    <ns541:para xmlns:ns541="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      After completing this course candidates should be able to
      <ns542:itemizedlist xmlns:ns542="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns543:listitem xmlns:ns543="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns544:para xmlns:ns544="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">understand the aim and benefits of MDA,</ns544:para></ns543:listitem>
        <ns545:listitem xmlns:ns545="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns546:para xmlns:ns546="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">understand how to practically implement <ns547:emphasis xmlns:ns547="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Model-Driven Enterprise Computing</ns547:emphasis>,</ns546:para></ns545:listitem>
        <ns548:listitem xmlns:ns548="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns549:para xmlns:ns549="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">model at different abstraction levels,</ns549:para></ns548:listitem>
        <ns550:listitem xmlns:ns550="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns551:para xmlns:ns551="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          have an understanding of the benefits of platform independent modeling (PIM),
        </ns551:para></ns550:listitem>
        <ns552:listitem xmlns:ns552="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns553:para xmlns:ns553="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          understand the mapping of the platform independent model onto the platform specific model (PSM),
        </ns553:para></ns552:listitem>
        <ns554:listitem xmlns:ns554="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns555:para xmlns:ns555="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          understand how one maps the platform specific model (PSM) onto the enterprise deployment model (EDM),
        </ns555:para></ns554:listitem>
        <ns556:listitem xmlns:ns556="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns557:para xmlns:ns557="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          understand the base technologies of MDA including UML 2.0, the Meta Object Facility (MOF), the XML MetaData Interchange (XMI)
          and the Object Constraint Language (OCL).
        </ns557:para></ns556:listitem>
        <ns558:listitem xmlns:ns558="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns559:para xmlns:ns559="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          defining contracts in the context of contract based software development,
        </ns559:para></ns558:listitem>
        <ns560:listitem xmlns:ns560="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns561:para xmlns:ns561="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          generate tests for contracts against which all realizations (class, service providers, ..) which implement the contract are tested against, and
        </ns561:para></ns560:listitem>
        <ns562:listitem xmlns:ns562="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns563:para xmlns:ns563="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          have an understanding of the tools which currently support MDA.
        </ns563:para></ns562:listitem>
      </ns542:itemizedlist>
    </ns541:para>
  </ns539:section>
  
  <ns564:section xmlns:ns564="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.solms.training.courses.MDA.coursePackage">
    <ns565:title xmlns:ns565="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Course Package</ns565:title>
    <ns566:para xmlns:ns566="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      Candidates will receive detailed lecture notes in the form of a bound book.
    </ns566:para>
  </ns564:section>

</ns528:section>